Michael L. Ford was named president of British Telecom Inc., a new post at the U.S. administration and investor-relations subsidiary of this telecommunications company.
He remains president of British Telecom International Inc., the U.S. sales and marketing arm.
Mr. Ford, 57 years old, is now in charge of all 100%-owned subsidiaries in the U.S., but not its partially held operations.
In June, John Carrington, formerly director of the mobile communications division, was named president of British Telecom Inc.
But he was subsequently offered a job at a competitor -- Mercury Communications Ltd. -- which he accepted, British Telecom said. 

